[[File:1896 Michigan football team.jpg|350px|thumb|right|1896 Michigan football team]]
The '''1896 Michigan Wolverines football team''' represented the [[University of Michigan]] in the [[college football]] season of 1896.  The team, with [[William Ward (American football)|William Ward]] as head coach, started the season with nine consecutive wins in which the Wolverines outscored their opponents by a combined score of 256 to 4.  In the final game of the season, played on Thanksgiving Day at the [[Chicago Coliseum]], the team lost a close game to [[Amos Alonzo Stagg]]'s [[University of Chicago]] team by a score of 7&ndash;6.  The 1896 Michigan&ndash;Chicago game was the first college football game played indoors, and the last portion of the game was also played under electric lights.  Henry M. Senter was the team captain.

